Interface JaxRx

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DOMJaxRx, TreeTankMediator

    public interface JaxRx
    This interface assembles all interface methods for the GET, POST, PUT and DELETE requests. [...]

    Sebastian Graf, Christian Gruen, Lukas Lewandowski, University of Konstanz

      • getParameters

        Set<QueryParameter> getParameters()
        This method returns all query parameters which are supported by the implementation.
        Returns:
        The Set containing the allowed parameters specified in QueryParameter.

      • command

        javax.ws.rs.core.StreamingOutput command(String command,
                                       ResourcePath path)
                                         throws JaxRxException
        This method is called by the GET and the POST method, if QueryParameter.COMMAND was specified in the HTTP request. This method performs a database command, based on the given resource path.
        Parameters:
        command - The command to be executed
        path - Resource and parameter info
        Returns:
        The StreamingOutput containing the query output.
        Throws:
        JaxRxException - thrown if
        • the specified resource does not exist (code 404)
        • the specified parameters are invalid or the command execution yields errors (code 400)
        • an unexpected exception occurs (code 500)

      • run

        javax.ws.rs.core.StreamingOutput run(String file,
                                   ResourcePath path)
                                     throws JaxRxException
        This method is called by the GET and the POST method, if QueryParameter.RUN was specified in the HTTP request. This method runs a server-side query file, based on the given resource path.
        Parameters:
        file - The file to be run
        path - Resource and parameter info
        Returns:
        The StreamingOutput containing the query output
        Throws:
        JaxRxException - thrown if
        • the specified resource or query file does not exist (status code: 404)
        • the specified parameters are invalid or the command execution yields errors (status code: 400)
        • an unexpected exception occurs (status code: 500)

      • query

        javax.ws.rs.core.StreamingOutput query(String query,
                                     ResourcePath path)
                                       throws JaxRxException
        This method is called by the GET and the POST method, if QueryParameter.QUERY was specified in the HTTP request. This method performs a query, based on the given resource path.
        Parameters:
        query - The query to be executed
        path - Resource and parameter info
        Returns:
        The StreamingOutput containing the query output.
        Throws:
        JaxRxException - thrown if
        • the specified resource does not exist (status code: 404)
        • the specified parameters are invalid or the query execution yields errors (status code: 400)
        • an unexpected exception occurs (status code: 500)

      • get

        javax.ws.rs.core.StreamingOutput get(ResourcePath path)
                                     throws JaxRxException
        This method is called by the GET and the POST method. The specified resource is returned. If no resource is specified, the root is returned, which can e.g. comprise a list of all resources.
        Parameters:
        path - Resource and parameter info
        Returns:
        The StreamingOutput containing the query output.
        Throws:
        JaxRxException - thrown if
        • the specified resource does not exist (status code: 404)
        • an unexpected exception occurs (status code: 500)

      • add

        String add(InputStream input,
         ResourcePath path)
           throws JaxRxException
        This method is called by the POST method. A new resource is added to the specified resource path.
        Parameters:
        input - The object containing the new content.
        path - Resource and parameter info
        Returns:
        info message
        Throws:
        JaxRxException - thrown if
        • the specified resource does not exist (status code: 404)
        • if the input is invalid (status code: 400)
        • an unexpected exception occurs (status code: 500)

      • update

        String update(InputStream input,
            ResourcePath path)
              throws JaxRxException
        This method is called by the PUT method. A new resource is created at the specified resource path. If the resource already exists, it is replaced by the new resource.
        Parameters:
        input - The incoming InputStream.
        path - Resource and parameter info
        Returns:
        info message
        Throws:
        JaxRxException - thrown if
        • the input was invalid (status code: 400)
        • an unexpected exception occurred (status code: 500)

      • delete

        String delete(ResourcePath path)
              throws JaxRxException
        This method is called by the DELETE method. An existing resource is deleted, which is specified by the resource path.
        Parameters:
        path - Resource and parameter info
        Returns:
        info message
        Throws:
        JaxRxException - thrown if
        • the resource was not found (status code: 404)
        • an unexpected exception occurred (status code: 500)
